                android:text="Make the Dough:

In a large bowl, combine the flour and salt. Add the cold, cubed butter and mix until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

Gradually add water and mix until the dough comes together. Knead the dough on a floured surface until smooth. Cover with plastic wrap and let it rest for at least 30 minutes.

Prepare the Filling:

In a pan, heat oil over medium heat. Sauté the onions and garlic until fragrant.

Add the ground meat and cook until browned.

Stir in the diced potatoes, carrots, and green peas. Cook until the vegetables are slightly tender.

Add soy sauce, curry powder (if using), raisins, salt, and pepper. Cook for a few more minutes until well combined. Adjust seasoning to taste. Allow the filling to cool.

Assemble the Empanadas:

Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).

Divide the dough into golf ball-sized portions. Roll each portion into a thin, round disc.

Place a spoonful of the filling in the center of each disc.

Fold the dough over the filling to form a half-moon shape. Press the edges to seal, and you can use a fork to crimp the edges for a decorative touch.

Beat an egg and brush the empanadas with the egg wash.

Bake or Fry the Empanadas:

For baking: Arrange the empanadas on a baking sheet and bake in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

For frying: Heat oil in a deep pan. Fry the empanadas until golden brown, turning them occasionally for even cooking.

Drain excess oil by placing the empanadas on a paper towel."
